<h4><span class="editsection">[<a href="/w/index.php?title=Mantra&amp;action=edit&amp;section=28" title="Edit section: Buddhist mantra calligraphy">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline">Buddhist mantra calligraphy</span></h4>
<ul>
<li><a href="http://www.visiblemantra.org/index.html" class="external text" title="http://www.visiblemantra.org/index.html" rel="nofollow">Buddhist Mantra Calligraphy</a> - mantras mainly in the <a href="/wiki/Siddham" title="Siddham" class="mw-redirect">Siddham</a> script, but also <a href="/wiki/Uchen" title="Uchen" class="mw-redirect">Uchen</a> (Tibetan), <a href="/w/index.php?title=Lantsa&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Lantsa (page does not exist)">Lantsa</a>. Some instruction.</li>
<li><a href="http://www.mandalar.com/DisplayJ/Bonji/index.html" class="external text" title="http://www.mandalar.com/DisplayJ/Bonji/index.html" rel="nofollow">Modern Siddham</a> - a comprehensive guide to the <a href="/wiki/Siddham" title="Siddham" class="mw-redirect">Siddham</a> script used for writing mantras in Japan.</li>
</ul>
